      "seed": 697585447,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 758431630,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776715456281,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "id": "cls1-desc",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 740,
      "y": 468,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 384,
      "text": "CLASS: FileTracker: Tracks file content hashes to detect changes\nbetween pipeline runs.\n\nMETHODS:\n+ from_state(state: dict[str, str]): Initialize from a previously\nsaved state dict.\n\n+ has_changed(file_path: str, content_hash: str): Check if a file's\ncontent has changed since last applied.\n\n+ mark_applied(file_path: str, content_hash: str): Record that a\nfile has been successfully processed.\n\n+ get_state(): Export current state for persistence.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "CLASS: FileTracker: Tracks file content hashes to detect changes\nbetween pipeline runs.\n\nMETHODS:\n+ from_state(state: dict[str, str]): Initialize from a previously\nsaved state dict.\n\n+ has_changed(file_path: str, content_hash: str): Check if a file's\ncontent has changed since last applied.\n\n+ mark_applied(file_path: str, content_hash: str): Record that a\nfile has been successfully processed.\n\n+ get_state(): Export current state for persistence.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 18
    }
  ],
